		<td><b>Billionaire Banshee NES version - party/social/tabletop game</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The party/social/tabletop card game Billionaire Banshee is being made into a NES game, converted by yours truly.<br />You may remember a post about BB here: viewtopic.php?f=2&amp;t=12702<br /><br />The guy just launched a Kickstarter with the NES version as one of the rewards. You can see a video of the NES version and original card game on this page: <a href="https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/razlo/billionaire-banshees-first-expansion?token=903c74a8" class="postlink">https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/razlo/billionaire-banshees-first-expansion?token=903c74a8</a><br /><br />This is a very unique project, and trying to show a video of a social/conversational game without seeing the human aspect (their discussions) makes it hard to represent what the real-world experience of the game is like, but hopefully the video of the current build gives a feel of the tone and style.<br /><br />The guy's vision for the project is to offer a social experience for the retro gaming community, especially since there aren't many tabletop or party games on the NES. <br /><br />The project is still in development, so any and all feedback is welcomed. I like to try to incorporate people's ideas and make things reach their full potential. There is also a single player mini game I'm working on for added play value. Thank you<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tJB6c9KADbA">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tJB6c9KADbA</a><!-- m -->

		

